    <h1>LaTeX to HTML with MathJax</h1>
    <p>This page renders LaTeX expressions using MathJax.</p>

    <div class="math-container">
        <p><h1>Step 1: Factor the denominators where possible to simplify the expression</h1>
<p>The given expression is \( \frac{x^2 - 31}{x^2 + 8x + 7} - \frac{x + 4}{x + 7} \). First, we notice that \( x^2 + 8x + 7 \) can be factored into \( (x + 7)(x + 1) \).</p>

<h1>Step 2: Rewrite the expression with the factored denominators</h1>
<p>The expression becomes \( \frac{x^2 - 31}{(x + 7)(x + 1)} - \frac{x + 4}{x + 7} \).</p>

<h1>Step 3: Find a common denominator for the two fractions to combine them</h1>
<p>To combine the fractions, we need a common denominator, which in this case is \( (x + 7)(x + 1) \). The second fraction can be rewritten as \( \frac{(x + 4)(x + 1)}{(x + 7)(x + 1)} \).</p>

<h1>Step 4: Combine the fractions</h1>
<p>Now, the expression is \( \frac{x^2 - 31}{(x + 7)(x + 1)} - \frac{(x + 4)(x + 1)}{(x + 7)(x + 1)} = \frac{x^2 - 31 - (x + 4)(x + 1)}{(x + 7)(x + 1)} \).</p>

<h1>Step 5: Simplify the numerator</h1>
<p>Expanding the numerator, we have \( x^2 - 31 - (x^2 + 5x + 4) \). Simplifying this gives \( x^2 - 31 - x^2 - 5x - 4 = -5x - 35 \).</p>

<h1>Step 6: Write the simplified expression</h1>
<p>The simplified expression is \( \frac{-5x - 35}{(x + 7)(x + 1)} \).</p>

<h1>Step 7: Factor out any common factors in the numerator and denominator</h1>
<p>We can factor out \( -5 \) from the numerator, resulting in \( \frac{-5(x + 7)}{(x + 7)(x + 1)} \).</p>

<h1>Step 8: Cancel any common factors between the numerator and denominator</h1>
<p>The \( (x + 7) \) in the numerator and denominator can be canceled out, leaving \( \frac{-5}{x + 1} \).</p>

<p>The final answer is: \( \boxed{-\frac{5}{x + 1}} \)</p>
</p>
